OL,3,CForecasters warn of more heavy snow
OL,4,Cacross swathes of northern Scotland
OL,6,FIn the yellow alert area, forecasters
OL,7,Fpredict that Grampian, the north-west
OL,8,FHighlands and Aberdeenshire will have
OL,9,Fthe most frequent snow showers on
OL,10,FMonday, with 5-10cm likely to fall
OL,11,Ffairly widely and a few places seeing
OL,12,F20-30cm.
OL,14,FOn Tuesday forecasters predict that a
OL,15,Ffurther 2-5cm of snow is likely to
OL,16,Ffall fairly widely, with the
OL,17,Fpossibility of a further 10-15cm in
OL,18,Fsome areas.
